
[1]affidavit

   AFFIDA'VIT, n. [An old law verb in the perfect tense; he made oath;
   from ad and fides, faith.]

   A declaration upon oath. In the United States, more generally, a
   declaration in writing, signed by the party, and sworn to, before an
   authorized magistrate.
